      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, by doing that (returning false) it exposed the issue in the previous (related) CL, that in SkTextBlob.cpp\u0027s SkTextBlobBuilder::ConservativeRunBounds there\u0027s code like\n\n    const SkRect fontBounds \u003d SkFontPriv::GetFontBounds(run.font());\n    if (fontBounds.isEmpty()) {\n        // Empty font bounds are likely a font bug.  TightBounds has a better chance of\n        // producing useful results in this case.\n        return TightRunBounds(run);\n    }\n\nand TightRunBounds wasn\u0027t handling RSXform.",
